data.title: Love the carnitas on the taco salad Pepsi products are a pluse.
data.text: This is a typical Mexican restaurant with the sombrero hats on the walls and meural paintings.The food is good.I had the taco salad with carnitas . You can choose the meat.There were fresh avocado and beans in this big taco shell along with lettues .The chips and salsa are fresh and made there.

data.title: Fun Place to Eat
data.text: This is a comfortable place to eat, better than fast food and  you can rejuvenate yourself from your travels.

data.title: It's a shame about that below average  mexican resturant in the good location.......
data.text: We have come to call it Café Deliciously average.....The drink came in different unmatched cups with our margarita flowing down the side. The utensils were still wet and so was the plate, this is not a good sign . The food had a blandness to it like it was masked/ fried  with old grease. It didn't have a identity at all. We ended up wishing we had gone to a small taquiria. The interior is not alive or really in good shape or clean....

data.title: Drop in and kick up your feet!
data.text: Romantic escape!  Great little "getaway" - Sip some ice-cold beers (or a margarita) & relax!!  Very "warm" environment & great comida mexicana!

data.title: Always a good meal
data.text: This is not an upscale Mexican Bistro. This is good old fashioned Mexican comfort food. Good service and good price. You can't go wrong for lunch or dinner

data.title: Horrible
data.text: One positive is the place was clean. I ordered a wine margarita and was not told the blender was broken so it was on the rocks (not a big deal). The people in the kitchen were talking so incredibly loud it was impossible to have a conversation with my son! The salad came out floating in ranch water in old wooden bowls, the salsa had a dish soap taste. My son has never left a Mexican restaurant without cleaning his plate and on this restaurant visit he ate very little. We have come here several times because my mom enjoys it so I have never left a review, but today was above and beyond unacceptable. They could see in the kitchen that they had costumers and just went on yelling, laughing and being rude. Never again! Our waitress was very friendly and I could tell she felt uncomfortable with the situation in the kitchen.

data.title: Greasy, sad food
data.text: This place was really disappointing.  Everything was too greasy and salty and nothing was special or unique.  With so many options for Mexican food in this area, diners should go somewhere else.

data.title: Great Mexican Food
data.text: The food was excellent as well as the staff.  I live in So. Cal. where there are a lot of great mexican restaurants and Cafe Delicias is as good as any I've visited over the last 50 years. Mike, owner, was very gracious and friendly. It was so good I went back 2 days later and ate there again on my 3 day visit to the Sacramento area. I will be back.

data.title: Absolutely Disgusting
data.text: I wish I new where the food came from that they used to take these beautiful pictures of but what they served was disgusting. All I wanted was a couple of tacos but we should have gone to Taco Bell instead of this place. I can only hope I don't get sick.

data.title: Good and authentic
data.text: Always great service and good food at this authentic Mexican restaurant. Its nothing fancy, but the food is hot and the cervezas are cold. Very reliable food quality and the family owned restaurant has been part of the community for years. Multiple locations.

data.title: consistently good Mexican Food
data.text: the tacos are the best I've ever had. We go to Cafe D at least once a month, sometimes more. We have lived in the area for 23 years, so that's a lot of visits.

data.title: Great Cheap Mexican Food
data.text: Bright orange vinyl newly reupholstered booths (so apparently somebody actually CHOSE that color), air conditioning that doesn’t seem to quite keep up, and waitresses that often seem a bit overworked.  Do I recommend this restaurant – ABSOLUTELY. Great cheap Mexican food at great prices and quick service.  I love this restaurant!  If you want ambiance and froofy cocktails – go someplace else and spend three times as much!  And actually, have you BEEN to Mexico?! – This ambiance is probably closer to authentic Mexican than most places out there… think about it!

data.title: Much better than other reviewers portray it !  The real deal.
data.text: I've been there three times now.  Each time the restaurant was spotless, and the service was excellent.  I have been to many little restaurants in Mexico, and this reminds me very much of those.  I keep expecting to see the grandma sitting over in the corner hand making the tortillas.  This is not a glitzy gringo style place, and I think that's a good thing.  And they serve Negra Modello.

data.title: And People Go There
data.text:
Well, I know mexican food. I would not bring my Mom or Dad here. Food was disappointing.  
Service was average.

data.title: really really cheap food...
data.text: really really cheap food and its really good! me and my room mate love this place! haha

data.title: It's a dive...
data.text:
My last experience at Cafe Delicious was terrible.  Both the inside and outside were very dirty; outside was trash, litter and produce boxes strewn about.  Inside, there were straw wrappers, napkins, etc. on the floor, glass cabinets smudged all over with greasy fingerprints and who knows what.  There were only two other diners in the entire restaurant, but 3 tables were not cleaned off.  There were at least 2 waitstaff, so this mess was inexcusable.   Speaking of waitstaff, ours was the stereotypical loud gum chewing, unkempt, dirty apron type.  The furniture was worn out.  Tape on the holes, padding to the springs, table tops worn down to an unintended multi-color look.

The food was only so-so.  I wondered if there was anything wrong with it; I shuddered to think what the kitchen was like.  I'm sure this is NOT what the founding family had in mind.

I won't go back.
